INSERT INTO `comments` VALUES (1,'Very useful tutorials. Hope more wonderful stuff. ','Wonderful','sddlzz@163.com',NULL,7,'2008-03-11 12:12:03',1,'Wonderful'),(2,'how do you limit the image size in your example?\nI mean if you use attachment_fu or something else you can easily \nlimit the image file size as well.\nI am using the same idea as yours, but did not get the file size problem right.','upload image','zhangpeng715@hotmail.com',NULL,2,'2008-03-24 22:41:35',1,'peter'),(3,'Very Beneficial resource code.','Very Beneficial','tomomikyoko@gmail.com',NULL,1,'2008-04-03 04:06:51',1,'Tomomi'),(4,'This is perfect!  Just what I was needing right now! You are my hero.\n\n','Fantastic!','len@lenwhite.com',NULL,6,'2008-04-12 12:27:37',1,'len'),(5,'beneficial','migrate','tuwatu@gmail.com',NULL,1,'2008-04-23 23:05:22',1,'tom'),(6,'Thank you for the organized approach to looking at migrations - much appreciated. One small item - I noticed in the PDF version, the rename_column item uses rename_table in the code example (rename_table :old_column_name, :new_column_name). ','Very nice - one small bug','joelewis@gmial.com',NULL,1,'2008-05-02 16:13:48',1,'Joe Lewis'),(7,'Do you have any plans to update the migration cheatsheet with this new information?  I think it is a great resource, but it would be even better if it included the new Rails 2.0 migration conventions.','update migrations cheatsheet?','nobody@nowhere.com',NULL,7,'2008-05-07 10:47:58',1,'nobody'),(8,'Fantastic article.  I used this in conjunction with rmagick and lightbox to get a rich photo handling UI.  Worked very well!','Excellent article!','rbgrn@rbgrn.net',NULL,2,'2008-06-20 12:22:03',1,'Robert Green'),(9,'Thanks, this is just what I needed!','Very Helpful','smithbm@masters.edu',NULL,2,'2008-06-22 22:45:22',1,'Brad'),(10,'Such an elegant and quick solution!!!  Thankyou','Elegant','graeme@privacy.net',NULL,2,'2008-06-29 09:48:16',1,'Graeme'),(11,'Thanks for your help!','Very nice!','redhat.lesi@gmail.com',NULL,2,'2008-06-29 21:49:12',1,'Jorge Barbosa'),(14,'How can I validate  the presence of image_file?','Help me please!','redhat.lesi@gmail.com',NULL,2,'2008-07-03 12:59:23',1,'Jorge Barbosa'),(15,'When I not fill the field  image_file appear this error:\nundefined method `original_filename\'\n\nAnd I put \"validate_presence_of: image_file\" in my \"model\"\n\nWhat is a problem?\n\n','Error','redhat.lesi@gmail.com',NULL,2,'2008-07-03 13:13:19',1,'Jorge Barbosa'),(16,'This is just what I was looking for.  I didn\'t want to be limited by the popular attachment plugins out there.  Thanks for writing this up!','Wonderful!','eleeconsulting@yahoo.com',NULL,2,'2008-07-03 23:36:31',1,'Eric'),(17,'Very nice, buy one type is missing. It\'s :text. Representing TEXT in mysql.','Very nice, buy one type is missing','cvetkovicbojan@gmail.com',NULL,1,'2008-07-04 14:46:49',1,'Cwelle'),(18,'Hello,\n       very interesting and very useful lessons. i learn lots of thinks from this codes. Also add lessons for controller and model part.','About Controllers','rcjagan@yahoo.co.in',NULL,9,'2008-07-11 11:29:21',1,'Jagannathan Sundaram'),(19,'thanks for this nice article....','Thanks','vinayji@ymail.com',NULL,8,'2008-07-14 04:51:28',1,'vinay'),(20,'What about drops for migrating down','Drops?','daniel-craig@hotmail.co.uk',NULL,1,'2008-07-15 07:19:35',1,'Dougle'),(21,'Any ideas on how to fix the following?\n\nDEPRECATION WARNING: paginate is deprecated and will be removed from Rails 2.0 (Pagination is moving to a plugin in Rails 2.0: script/plugin install svn://errtheblog.com/svn/plugins/classic_pagination)  See http://www.rubyonrails.org/deprecation for details. (called from list at /rails/gtown/app/controllers/photo_admin_controller.rb:12)\n','Rails 2.0','nmercer@noiseable.com',NULL,2,'2008-07-18 12:45:32',1,'Nicholas Mercer'),(22,'Sorry, posted wrong error message.....  DEPRECATION WARNING: You\'ve called image_path with a source that doesn\'t include an extension. In Rails 2.0, that will not result in .png automatically being appended. So you should call image_path(\'/photo_admin/code_image/3.png\') instead  See http://www.rubyonrails.org/deprecation for details. (called from image_tag at /rails/gtown/vendor/rails/actionpack/lib/action_view/helpers/asset_tag_helper.rb:188)','Rails 2.0','nmercer@noiseable.com',21,2,'2008-07-18 12:46:14',1,'Nicholas Mercer'),(23,'the image odes nit appear, instead a description, content type, filename and time of creation appears... could you help me with this one','rails2.0','ajibanda@yahoo.com',NULL,2,'2008-07-28 00:27:29',1,'aj illescas'),(24,'what ahout a little bit of courtesy?\nSo, when you find an excelent guide to migrations, the only thing to say is \"What about drops for migrating down\"\n\npff...','Cortesy','mr.skorpio@gmail.com',20,1,'2008-07-30 07:20:02',1,'txarli'),(25,'\"So, when you find an excelent guide to migrations, the only thing to say is \"What about drops for migrating down\" pff...\"\n\nExactly what i mean.. it would be an \"excellent\" guide if it had drop syntax, that\'s not discourteous at all.','Drops?','daniel-craig@hotmail.co.uk',24,1,'2008-07-30 10:39:08',1,'Dougle'),(26,'This tutorial was exactly what I needed to get me started. My application needed attachments, and this helped me figure out the file upload portion. From there, it wasn\'t too hard to figure out how to associate the files with my other records, and I\'m in business.\n\nYour step-by-step directions made this much easier than fiddling with one of the attachment plugins (and I\'m speaking from frustrating experience here! :) ).','Thanks for this resource!','sarah@findableblogs.com',NULL,2,'2008-08-11 17:18:17',1,'Sarah Lewis'),(27,'I am now bald and lost about 20 pounds....\nbut when I finally added \"has_many :image_files\" to the class declaration in app/models/photo.rb, I can now load am image properly into the db.\n','this failed for me until...','seymour.krebs@gmail.com',NULL,2,'2008-08-13 14:53:52',1,'sgk'),(28,'Thanks for this very useful resource.\n\nThe args for rename_table should be :old_table, :new_table (and rename_table is actually listed twice too).','rename_table args reversed','gideon@novamind.com',NULL,1,'2008-08-18 22:25:37',1,'Gideon'),(29,'You\'re missing the table argument from the rename_column syntax as well.\n','rename_column is wrong too','hotpron@mail.com',NULL,1,'2008-08-26 12:56:45',1,'Ryan Shillington'),(30,'What are all the content types?','content type','andrew@elancommunications.net',NULL,13,'2008-09-02 16:43:36',1,'Andrew Degenhardt'),(31,'It would probably be useful to mention the version of Rails with which this code has been successfully tested.','Rails Version','none@nowhere.net',NULL,2,'2008-09-03 15:25:16',1,'observer'),(32,'In \"Fixtures\" section, item 4, \"migration.rb\" was swapped with \"customers.yml\".\n','Minor mistake','mosquete@bol.com.br',NULL,1,'2008-09-04 15:49:54',1,'mosquete'),(33,'Thanks for the cheatsheet!\n\nAnd here\'s some feedback: I think the \"Visual representation of params\" is unnecessary. The description of \"params[]\" just above it leaves no doubt about the organization of its content. So that space could be used for something else.','Visual representation not necessary','mosquete@bol.com.br',NULL,8,'2008-09-08 20:38:13',1,'mosquete'),(36,'I recently needed to do this for a pretty static site and didn\'t really want to use attachment_fu this time, so I used this as a guideline to see if I could do it. Based on previous comments I wasn\'t sure what the problems would be, but I had minimal problems, and they were all do to simple copy/paste errors (since I\'m not doing quite the same thing). I have models, lets call them Animals, and they has_many photos (with photos being set up basically as above). Photos belongs_to Animals. Photo.rb has the def image_file=(input_data)\n code from above. In my animals controller I did add @photo = Photo.new(params[:photo])\n in the create action, and @photo = Photo.new in the new action (I